<item>
            <title>[LU-14959] Users of ldlm_resource_get much check return value</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14959</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;osc_req_attr_set() and mdc_get_lock_handle() use result from ldlm_resource_get() without checking it&apos;s not IS_ERR() resulting in a NULL pointer dereference crash in ldlm_resource_dump()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s less critical in osc_req_attr_set where the branch culminates in LBUG anyway, but mdc_get_lock_handle seems to be a real unintended crash.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Both cases seem to be worth fixing and also comment for ldlm_resource_get is incorrect since it no longer returns NULL for the error&lt;/p&gt;</description>
